The paper discusses a measure of quality for Linked Data concepts and focuses on the issue of semantic decay caused by the reuse of concepts. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the development of more advanced Semantic Web applications, databases (cs.DB) for the management of Linked Data resources, social and information networks (cs.SI) for the propagation of semantic information on the Web, information retrieval (cs.IR) for the search and retrieval of high-quality Linked Data, and machine learning (cs.LG) for the development of models to address the scalability problem.
